Rating: 4
This recipe turns out perfectly and is a must for the chocolate lover. It will look and taste incredibly professional. Those ending up with a dry cake are not following the recipe correctly. I watched the cake very closely and took it out as soon as the tester came out clean, I used regular buttermilk, not low fat/yoghurt/sourcream, and I wrapped the cakes tightly with plastic wrap after they had completely cooled. Not doing the above may be the reason behind a dry cake. Definately drain the raspberries (frozen work perfectly and they are much more affordable). I also used blackberry brandy instead of raspberry as it was available in a much smaller size. I also used all of the cake and made 3 layers instead of 2. I didn't need to increase the filling but I increased the glaze by 1/2 and it was just enough for each layer and the cake sides. I only used whipped cream for the top. Enjoy!

